00:45:19.384 --> 00:45:20.676
I didn't get a lot of sleep.

684
00:45:20.677 --> 00:45:23.429
Big power outage knocked out
my alarm clock.

685
00:45:23.430 --> 00:45:24.430
Won't happen again.

686
00:45:24.431 --> 00:45:25.806
No, I didn't sleep either.

687
00:45:25.807 --> 00:45:27.808
What kept you awake?

688
00:45:27.809 --> 00:45:29.811
Doesn't matter.

689
00:45:32.188 --> 00:45:33.523
You're under attack.

690
00:45:35.567 --> 00:45:38.277
What are you talking about?

691
00:45:38.278 --> 00:45:40.488
You're in
a spiritual battle, Erin.

692
00:45:40.489 --> 00:45:42.490
The forces of darkness
are trying to keep you

693
00:45:42.491 --> 00:45:43.992
away from the light.

694
00:45:45.285 --> 00:45:46.369
Don't let them.

695
00:45:48.037 --> 00:45:52.458
Don't worry about today.
We're doing fine.

696
00:45:52.459 --> 00:45:53.917
We're getting creamed.

697
00:45:53.918 --> 00:45:55.670
I can't believe it,
I walked right into that.

698
00:45:55.671 --> 00:45:57.546
Look, if we don't find
a doctor to testify

699
00:45:57.547 --> 00:46:01.175
that Emily wasn't...
epileptic or schizophrenic

700
00:46:01.176 --> 00:46:02.801
or... schizo-epileptic,

701
00:46:02.802 --> 00:46:04.554
we're gonna lose.

702
00:46:06.806 --> 00:46:09.726
[WIND WHISTLING]

703
00:46:12.479 --> 00:46:15.772
Care of the city's main branch
and the university library,

704
00:46:15.773 --> 00:46:18.066
I bring you another dozen
fun-filled books

705
00:46:18.067 --> 00:46:22.904
about the demonic
and the mentally deranged.

706
00:46:22.905 --> 00:46:24.573
{\an8}They used to burn women
at the stake

707
00:46:24.574 --> 00:46:26.908
{\an8}during witch hunts
for being demon-possessed.

708
00:46:26.909 --> 00:46:28.910
Be glad you don't have
to defend those guys.

709
00:46:28.911 --> 00:46:30.705
How we doing
on our medical experts?

710
00:46:30.706 --> 00:46:32.289
Not good.

711
00:46:32.290 --> 00:46:35.000
The psychiatrist you wanted
is tied up in another trial.

712
00:46:35.001 --> 00:46:38.837
And the neurologist
is sailing to Costa Rica.

713
00:46:38.838 --> 00:46:41.423
This book I'm reading
is by an anthropologist.

714
00:46:41.424 --> 00:46:44.259
It's about contemporary cases
of possession,

715
00:46:44.260 --> 00:46:45.844
mostly in the Third World.

716
00:46:45.845 --> 00:46:48.305
Of course, people there are
primitive and superstitious.

717
00:46:48.306 --> 00:46:52.142
Maybe. Maybe they see possession
for what it really is.

718
00:46:52.143 --> 00:46:54.770
Maybe we've taught ourselves
not to see it.

719
00:46:54.771 --> 00:46:57.523
Are you saying
you believe in this stuff?

720
00:46:57.524 --> 00:46:58.940
No.

721
00:46:58.941 --> 00:47:00.859
I'm saying maybe
we shouldn't just try

722
00:47:00.860 --> 00:47:02.695
to invalidate
the prosecution's case

723
00:47:02.696 --> 00:47:04.863
by punching holes
in the medical approach.

724
00:47:04.864 --> 00:47:08.075
Maybe we should also try...

725
00:47:08.076 --> 00:47:09.952
to validate the alternative.

726
00:47:11.747 --> 00:47:13.247
[SIGHS]

727
00:47:13.248 --> 00:47:16.250
Validate possession...
in a court of law.

728
00:47:16.251 --> 00:47:17.292
Yes.

729
00:47:17.293 --> 00:47:19.378
[♪♪♪]

730
00:47:19.379 --> 00:47:22.047
Okay. I guess we could
bring in some priests to talk

731
00:47:22.048 --> 00:47:24.508
about exorcisms that they've
performed, if we can find any.

732
00:47:24.509 --> 00:47:26.218
No, the archdiocese
won't let us do that.

733
00:47:26.219 --> 00:47:28.387
They wanna limit the Church's
exposure to Father Moore

734
00:47:28.388 --> 00:47:29.846
and no one else.

735
00:47:29.847 --> 00:47:31.848
But I've got three articles
by the anthropologist

736
00:47:31.849 --> 00:47:33.141
who wrote this book.

737
00:47:33.142 --> 00:47:35.018
She approaches
the subject of possession

738
00:47:35.019 --> 00:47:36.520
from a scientific perspective

739
00:47:36.521 --> 00:47:38.397
and doesn't try to debunk it.

740
00:47:38.398 --> 00:47:39.565
You want me to track her down?

741
00:47:39.566 --> 00:47:42.526
Yeah.

742
00:47:42.527 --> 00:47:45.696
Keep looking for a medical
expert to refute Dr. Briggs.

743
00:47:45.697 --> 00:47:48.784
But send the case file
to this Dr. Sadira Adani.

744
00:47:50.076 --> 00:47:52.745
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

745
00:47:52.746 --> 00:47:54.996
as you know by now,
my name is Erin Bruner,

746
00:47:54.997 --> 00:47:57.833
and I represent the defendant,
Richard Moore.

747
00:47:57.834 --> 00:48:00.001
Mr. Thomas has contended

748
00:48:00.002 --> 00:48:04.089
that Emily Rose suffered from
a serious medical condition

749
00:48:04.090 --> 00:48:07.426
that required medical treatment,
nothing more.

750
00:48:07.427 --> 00:48:10.887
He has asserted
that any attempt by my client

751
00:48:10.888 --> 00:48:13.682
to help Emily by anything
other than medical means

752
00:48:13.683 --> 00:48:17.978
was not only inappropriate,
but criminally negligent.

753
00:48:17.979 --> 00:48:20.648
I'm now gonna ask

754
00:48:20.649 --> 00:48:22.483
that you keep an open mind

755
00:48:22.484 --> 00:48:25.861
to what our evidence
and testimony will show.

756
00:48:25.862 --> 00:48:28.405
Medical treatment was
not the answer for Emily,

757
00:48:28.406 --> 00:48:32.701
because she simply did not
suffer from a medical condition.

758
00:48:32.702 --> 00:48:37.791
She was neither epileptic,
nor psychotic.

759
00:48:40.001 --> 00:48:43.712
Emily Rose's condition, in fact,
was demonic possession.

760
00:48:43.713 --> 00:48:46.799
An exorcism was her only hope
for a cure.

761
00:48:46.800 --> 00:48:48.425
Some of you may find yourself

762
00:48:48.426 --> 00:48:51.553
unable to reconcile
Emily's beliefs,

763
00:48:51.554 --> 00:48:53.597
or those of the defendant,
with your own.

764
00:48:53.598 --> 00:48:56.933
You may not believe
demons exist.

765
00:48:56.934 --> 00:48:58.435
You won't have to.

766
00:48:58.436 --> 00:49:00.979
Because you will see
that after the utter failure

767
00:49:00.980 --> 00:49:02.690
of the doctors to help Emily,

768
00:49:02.691 --> 00:49:06.694
Father Moore simply tried to
help Emily in a different way,

769
00:49:06.695 --> 00:49:11.365
using an approach that he,
Emily, <i>and</i> her family

770
00:49:11.366 --> 00:49:14.409
firmly believed was
her only chance for relief.

771
00:49:14.410 --> 00:49:17.663
And we will show that
despite his greatest efforts,

772
00:49:17.664 --> 00:49:19.832
and his sincere love for Emily,

773
00:49:19.833 --> 00:49:22.751
<i>there was absolutely nothing
Father Richard Moore</i>

774
00:49:22.752 --> 00:49:26.589
<i>could have done to prevent
the death of Emily Rose.</i>

775
00:49:29.551 --> 00:49:30.927
You okay?

776
00:49:32.929 --> 00:49:34.430
Aren't you gonna eat anything?

777
00:49:35.181 --> 00:49:37.057
[GIRL LAUGHS]

778
00:49:37.058 --> 00:49:38.935
[♪♪♪]

779
00:49:43.773 --> 00:49:45.775
[DISTORTED CHATTER]

780
00:49:48.236 --> 00:49:51.406
[ICE CUBES CLINKING]

781
00:49:53.157 --> 00:49:55.911
[CUTLERY SCRAPING]

782
00:50:07.422 --> 00:50:09.047
JASON:
<i>She said it was terrible</i>

783
00:50:09.048 --> 00:50:12.175
<i>to hear the clinking
of spoons and forks.</i>

784
00:50:12.176 --> 00:50:13.594
She was always hungry,

785
00:50:13.595 --> 00:50:15.555
but she said
they wouldn't let her eat.

786
00:50:16.598 --> 00:50:18.849
Who did she mean by "they"?

787
00:50:18.850 --> 00:50:22.728
The forces that were
in control of her.

788
00:50:22.729 --> 00:50:25.940
That were, uh, inside her.

789
00:50:25.941 --> 00:50:28.401
Uh, you know,
the... The demons.

790
00:50:30.069 --> 00:50:32.655
Tell us what else happened
that night.

791
00:50:36.200 --> 00:50:39.661
I walked her back to her dorm.

792
00:50:39.662 --> 00:50:42.372
And she seemed
really nervous and scared.

793
00:50:42.373 --> 00:50:45.542
<i>So I held her for a while,
trying to calm her down.</i>

794
00:50:45.543 --> 00:50:49.337
<i>I fell asleep,
but when I woke up,</i>

795
00:50:49.338 --> 00:50:51.757
<i>she wasn't beside me.</i>

796
00:50:51.758 --> 00:50:53.760
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

797
00:50:57.806 --> 00:50:59.055
[♪♪♪]

798
00:50:59.056 --> 00:51:02.184
[PANTING]

799
00:51:05.021 --> 00:51:06.272
Emily?

800
00:51:18.910 --> 00:51:20.745
Hey.

801
00:51:24.540 --> 00:51:25.834
Can you hear me?

802
00:51:31.547 --> 00:51:34.550
[DISTORTED HOWL]

803
00:51:38.095 --> 00:51:39.513
JASON:
<i>I called her father,</i>

804
00:51:39.514 --> 00:51:41.223
<i>and he told me
to bring Emily home.</i>

805
00:51:43.768 --> 00:51:46.269
MR. ROSE:
<i>Jason and I put Emily to bed,</i>

806
00:51:46.270 --> 00:51:48.396
<i>hoping she would sleep.</i>

807
00:51:48.397 --> 00:51:50.650
And when did Father Moore
become involved?

808
00:51:52.109 --> 00:51:54.319
Emily stayed home after that.

809
00:51:54.320 --> 00:51:57.155
She didn't return to school,
and she kept getting worse.

810
00:51:57.156 --> 00:52:00.325
Eventually,
when she didn't get better,

811
00:52:00.326 --> 00:52:01.368
we called our priest,

812
00:52:01.369 --> 00:52:03.161
Father Moore.

813
00:52:03.162 --> 00:52:05.205
When he arrived,

814
00:52:05.206 --> 00:52:07.165
<i>I sent my daughter,
Alice, upstairs</i>

815
00:52:07.166 --> 00:52:10.086
<i>to see if Emily was awake.</i>

816
00:52:12.421 --> 00:52:14.883
[EMILY GRUNTING]

817
00:52:17.343 --> 00:52:18.927
EMILY [GRUNTING]:
...in heaven...

818
00:52:18.928 --> 00:52:20.428
Emily?

819
00:52:20.429 --> 00:52:23.348
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

820
00:52:23.349 --> 00:52:24.850
Can I come in?

821
00:52:24.851 --> 00:52:27.602
EMILY [GRUNTING]:
Give us this day our daily bread.

822
00:52:27.603 --> 00:52:30.689
And forgive us our trespasses,

823
00:52:30.690 --> 00:52:35.360
as we forgive those

824
00:52:35.361 --> 00:52:39.073
who trespass against us.

825
00:52:39.074 --> 00:52:41.157
Our Father, who art in heaven...

826
00:52:41.158 --> 00:52:42.910
Emily?

827
00:52:42.911 --> 00:52:45.245
[SQUISHING]

828
00:52:45.246 --> 00:52:46.997
Thy will be done...

829
00:52:46.998 --> 00:52:49.917
Father Moore is here.
Can you come downstairs?

830
00:52:49.918 --> 00:52:52.419
...on earth as it is in heaven.

831
00:52:52.420 --> 00:52:54.588
Give us this day

832
00:52:54.589 --> 00:52:57.465
our daily bread.

833
00:52:57.466 --> 00:52:58.551
[SCREAMS]

834
00:52:59.427 --> 00:53:00.469
[STIFLED SCREAM]

835
00:53:02.179 --> 00:53:03.598
[SCREECHES]

836
00:53:05.391 --> 00:53:08.351
[♪♪♪]

837
00:53:08.352 --> 00:53:10.146
MR. ROSE:
Emily!

838
00:53:13.983 --> 00:53:15.110
[SHRIEKS]

839
00:53:19.822 --> 00:53:20.907
[SCREAMS]

840
00:53:23.534 --> 00:53:25.578
[SHRIEKING]

841
00:53:39.759 --> 00:53:42.385
[PANTING]

842
00:53:42.386 --> 00:53:43.804
Emily, can you hear me?

843
00:53:43.805 --> 00:53:48.726
[SPEAKS LATIN
IN DISTORTED VOICE]

844
00:53:49.477 --> 00:53:51.312
[BONES CRACKING]

845
00:53:59.487 --> 00:54:01.363
Let's get her off the floor.

846
00:54:02.490 --> 00:54:03.574
Alice, no.

847
00:54:04.659 --> 00:54:07.120
[ALICE SOBBING]

848
00:54:16.462 --> 00:54:19.882
[IN LATIN] I am the one
who dwells within.

849
00:54:21.801 --> 00:54:26.181
[IN LATIN] And I am the one
who comes in His name.

850
00:54:27.515 --> 00:54:31.810
Think you can force me out,
priest?

851
00:54:31.811 --> 00:54:32.811
[TEETH CLICK, GRUNTS]

852
00:54:32.812 --> 00:54:34.147
Try.

853
00:54:35.898 --> 00:54:37.983
I dare you.

854
00:54:37.984 --> 00:54:39.401
[BONES CRACK]

855
00:54:40.778 --> 00:54:42.530
[WHIMPERING]

856
00:54:48.828 --> 00:54:50.538
[GROWLS]

857
00:54:51.998 --> 00:54:53.290
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

858
00:55:26.157 --> 00:55:28.993
[PIANO PLAYING RACHMANINOFF'S
PRELUDE OP. 3 NO. 2]

859
00:55:39.628 --> 00:55:41.922
THOMAS: You've suffered
a terrible loss, Mr. Rose.

860
00:55:41.923 --> 00:55:43.006
I know this is difficult,

861
00:55:43.007 --> 00:55:45.508
so thank you
for being here today.

862
00:55:45.509 --> 00:55:47.010
Sir, do you often
read the Bible?

863
00:55:47.011 --> 00:55:48.053
Yes, I do.

864
00:55:48.054 --> 00:55:49.222
So do I.

865
00:55:49.889 --> 00:55:52.224
What about the <i>DSM?</i>

866
00:55:52.225 --> 00:55:55.102
The <i>Diagnostic and Statistical
Manual of Mental Disorders.</i>

867
00:55:55.103 --> 00:55:57.687
Commonly referred to as the
bible of abnormal psychiatry.

868
00:55:57.688 --> 00:55:59.231
Have you read that?

869
00:55:59.232 --> 00:56:02.109
No. So you're not aware
that, according to the <i>DSM,</i>

870
00:56:02.110 --> 00:56:03.484
a person's refusal to eat

871
00:56:03.485 --> 00:56:05.653
is a common indication
of a psychiatric condition

872
00:56:05.654 --> 00:56:06.738
known as anorexia?

873
00:56:06.739 --> 00:56:08.573
Objection.
The witness just said

874
00:56:08.574 --> 00:56:10.408
he hasn't read the <i>DSM,</i>
Your Honor.

875
00:56:10.409 --> 00:56:11.492
Sustained.

876
00:56:11.493 --> 00:56:12.994
Mr. Rose...

877
00:56:12.995 --> 00:56:15.705
are you aware that
catatonic rigidity,

878
00:56:15.706 --> 00:56:18.041
specifically a locking up
of the joints of the body,

879
00:56:18.042 --> 00:56:20.043
is a known symptom of psychosis?

880
00:56:20.044 --> 00:56:22.629
No. I haven't studied
these things.

881
00:56:22.630 --> 00:56:24.881
Have you ever visited
an insane asylum,

882
00:56:24.882 --> 00:56:27.425
or a hospital for the treatment
of the mentally ill?

883
00:56:27.426 --> 00:56:30.637
Once. My aunt was in one
before she died.

884
00:56:30.638 --> 00:56:32.806
Really? So there's a history

885
00:56:32.807 --> 00:56:34.141
of mental illness
in your family?

886
00:56:34.142 --> 00:56:35.809
I suppose.

887
00:56:35.810 --> 00:56:41.773
Sir, if you saw someone eating
insects on a street corner...

888
00:56:41.774 --> 00:56:44.067
would you say that
that person is mentally ill?

889
00:56:44.068 --> 00:56:45.277
Probably, yes.

890
00:56:45.278 --> 00:56:46.903
So can you really say
with confidence

891
00:56:46.904 --> 00:56:48.613
that the behavior you saw

892
00:56:48.614 --> 00:56:50.991
in your daughter's bedroom that
night could not be the behavior

893
00:56:50.992 --> 00:56:52.575
of someone suffering
from psychosis?

894
00:56:52.576 --> 00:56:54.369
MR. ROSE:
I don't know.

895
00:56:54.370 --> 00:56:56.621
She never had any problems
like that before.

896
00:56:56.622 --> 00:57:02.043
It just didn't feel that way
to me... or to Father Moore.

897
00:57:02.044 --> 00:57:03.586
And you trusted him, right?

898
00:57:03.587 --> 00:57:06.214
Yes. He is
our parish priest.

899
00:57:06.215 --> 00:57:07.674
THOMAS:
Fair enough.

900
00:57:07.675 --> 00:57:09.634
And after that night,
would you say that you

901
00:57:09.635 --> 00:57:12.428
put your daughter entirely
in Father Moore's care?

902
00:57:12.429 --> 00:57:15.098
Yes. We had done all we could.

903
00:57:15.099 --> 00:57:17.642
We said she was
in his hands now,

904
00:57:17.643 --> 00:57:20.603
body and soul.

905
00:57:20.604 --> 00:57:22.022
THOMAS:
Thank you.

906
00:57:22.023 --> 00:57:24.107
No further questions,
Your Honor.

907
00:57:24.108 --> 00:57:26.319
JUDGE: Thank you, Mr. Rose.
You may step down.

908
00:57:28.237 --> 00:57:31.239
The defense calls
Dr. Sadira Adani.

909
00:57:31.240 --> 00:57:33.325
ADANI:
I am currently a professor

910
00:57:33.326 --> 00:57:38.079
of anthropology and psychiatry
at Northwestern University.

911
00:57:38.080 --> 00:57:39.664
Where did you receive
your education?

912
00:57:39.665 --> 00:57:42.292
At Yale, and then at Cambridge.

913
00:57:42.293 --> 00:57:44.794
And what is your specific area
of expertise?

914
00:57:44.795 --> 00:57:47.214
I study
the spiritual experiences

915
00:57:47.215 --> 00:57:49.299
of people in various cultures,

916
00:57:49.300 --> 00:57:52.677
and the physiological
and psychological changes

917
00:57:52.678 --> 00:57:56.472
they undergo
during these experiences.

918
00:57:56.473 --> 00:57:58.641
Would it be accurate to say
that you specialize

919
00:57:58.642 --> 00:58:00.643
in the scientific study
of possession?

920
00:58:00.644 --> 00:58:05.648
Yes. Possession is one term
for a basic human experience

921
00:58:05.649 --> 00:58:10.778
reported by a great number
of people all around the world.

922
00:58:10.779 --> 00:58:13.990
In my fieldwork,
I've seen many people

923
00:58:13.991 --> 00:58:17.160
who experienced
a sense of being invaded

924
00:58:17.161 --> 00:58:19.996
by an entity
from the supernatural realm.

925
00:58:19.997 --> 00:58:22.165
Why do you think Emily
was invaded?

926
00:58:22.166 --> 00:58:24.584
Why did this possession
happen to her?

927
00:58:24.585 --> 00:58:27.128
Based on my study
of the case file,

928
00:58:27.129 --> 00:58:31.341
I believe that Emily Rose
was a hypersensitive.

929
00:58:31.342 --> 00:58:34.302
A person
with an unusual connection

930
00:58:34.303 --> 00:58:38.139
to what Carlos Castaneda called
"the separate reality."

931
00:58:38.140 --> 00:58:43.311
Hypersensitives are born
different from everyone else.

932
00:58:43.312 --> 00:58:46.231
They can have visions
of the future

933
00:58:46.232 --> 00:58:47.523
or see the dead,

934
00:58:47.524 --> 00:58:50.860
and sometimes be
uniquely susceptible

935
00:58:50.861 --> 00:58:54.072
to invasion by an entity
that is alien to them.

936
00:58:54.073 --> 00:58:55.450
Objection.

937
00:58:56.533 --> 00:58:58.285
JUDGE:
On what grounds?

938
00:58:58.286 --> 00:59:00.412
How 'bout silliness, Your Honor?

939
00:59:00.413 --> 00:59:02.289
A young girl suffered
terribly and died.

940
00:59:02.290 --> 00:59:03.706
Do we have to subject
her illness

941
00:59:03.707 --> 00:59:06.418
to this...
pseudoscientific analysis?

942
00:59:06.419 --> 00:59:09.629
Both counselors,
please approach the bench.

943
00:59:09.630 --> 00:59:11.672
Your Honor, this testimony
is beyond ridiculous.

944
00:59:11.673 --> 00:59:13.508
[WHISPERING]
Visions of the future.

945
00:59:13.509 --> 00:59:16.428
[WHISPERS] Supernatural belief
systems are shared by millions,

946
00:59:16.429 --> 00:59:18.221
perhaps billions,
of people in the world.

947
00:59:18.222 --> 00:59:19.555
Her expertise
is directly relevant

948
00:59:19.556 --> 00:59:20.848
to the issues in this case.

949
00:59:20.849 --> 00:59:23.102
Let's bring in a witch doctor...
Stop.

950
00:59:27.398 --> 00:59:29.399
We've heard a great deal
of testimony

951
00:59:29.400 --> 00:59:31.401
in support
of a medical explanation

952
00:59:31.402 --> 00:59:33.569
for Emily's condition.

953
00:59:33.570 --> 00:59:36.072
Now, we have a witness
who has spent her career

954
00:59:36.073 --> 00:59:39.284
studying the defense's
alternative explanation.

955
00:59:39.285 --> 00:59:41.411
An exorcism expert, if you will.

956
00:59:41.412 --> 00:59:44.872
I think we'll hear
what she has to say.

957
00:59:44.873 --> 00:59:46.583
Thank you, Your Honor.

958
00:59:48.836 --> 00:59:50.962
Dr. Adani...

959
00:59:50.963 --> 00:59:53.507
why do you think
Emily's exorcism failed?

960
00:59:53.508 --> 00:59:55.800
The medical treatment,

961
00:59:55.801 --> 00:59:58.845
specifically,
the drug, Gambutrol.

962
00:59:58.846 --> 01:00:00.472
Please explain.

963
01:00:00.473 --> 01:00:04.976
The exorcism ritual results
in a specific brain activity

964
01:00:04.977 --> 01:00:08.980
that cuts the person off
from the possession experience.

965
01:00:08.981 --> 01:00:14.235
But Emily's exorcism
could not have achieved this

966
01:00:14.236 --> 01:00:17.030
because the doctor
gave her Gambutrol,

967
01:00:17.031 --> 01:00:20.908
which has an intoxicating effect
on the brain.

968
01:00:20.909 --> 01:00:25.163
The drug made her immune
to the psycho-spiritual shock

969
01:00:25.164 --> 01:00:28.291
that exorcism
is intended to provide.

970
01:00:28.292 --> 01:00:30.710
What do you believe was
the ultimate result of treatment

971
01:00:30.711 --> 01:00:32.379
with this intoxicating drug?

972
01:00:32.380 --> 01:00:36.257
Gambutrol locked Emily
in the possessed state.

973
01:00:36.258 --> 01:00:39.844
This left her unable
to respond to the exorcism.

974
01:00:39.845 --> 01:00:44.433
And therefore, it directly
contributed to her death.

975
01:00:45.809 --> 01:00:47.685
No further questions.

976
01:00:47.686 --> 01:00:49.646
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

977
01:00:51.232 --> 01:00:52.857
Erin!

978
01:00:52.858 --> 01:00:55.235
I've got a doctor
who wants to testify.

979
01:00:55.236 --> 01:00:58.530
He's an eyewitness, Erin.
He was there.

980
01:00:58.531 --> 01:00:59.697
He was at the exorcism.

981
01:00:59.698 --> 01:01:01.032
What?
He called us.

982
01:01:01.033 --> 01:01:02.576
Dr. Graham Cartwright,

983
01:01:02.577 --> 01:01:04.160
Department of Abnormal
Psychiatry

984
01:01:04.161 --> 01:01:05.329
at St. Mary's Hospital.

985
01:01:13.170 --> 01:01:16.672
Dr. Cartwright.
Ring a bell?

986
01:01:16.673 --> 01:01:18.674
Yes.

987
01:01:18.675 --> 01:01:20.760
He was there?

988
01:01:20.761 --> 01:01:21.844
Yes.

989
01:01:21.845 --> 01:01:24.556
Father...

990
01:01:24.557 --> 01:01:26.057
if you want me to defend you,

991
01:01:26.058 --> 01:01:29.143
you've got to give me
all the information I need.

992
01:01:29.144 --> 01:01:30.937
With all of
this medical testimony

993
01:01:30.938 --> 01:01:32.564
helping the prosecution,

994
01:01:32.565 --> 01:01:33.981
how could you not tell me

995
01:01:33.982 --> 01:01:35.943
that a doctor attended
the exorcism?

996
01:01:37.861 --> 01:01:42.115
He asked that I keep
his involvement confidential.

997
01:01:42.116 --> 01:01:43.659
And I said I would.

998
01:01:59.091 --> 01:02:01.301
Dr. Cartwright?

999
01:02:01.302 --> 01:02:03.177
Oh...

1000
01:02:03.178 --> 01:02:07.265
I recognize you from those
courtroom drawings on the news.

1001
01:02:07.266 --> 01:02:10.519
You're much prettier
in real life.

1002
01:02:11.853 --> 01:02:12.937
May I sit?

1003
01:02:12.938 --> 01:02:15.274
Uh, yes, please.

1004
01:02:21.447 --> 01:02:23.824
You're losing.

1005
01:02:25.618 --> 01:02:28.620
I had hoped Father Moore
wouldn't need me,

1006
01:02:28.621 --> 01:02:32.290
but I don't want
to see him put away.

1007
01:02:32.291 --> 01:02:33.833
How do you know him?

1008
01:02:33.834 --> 01:02:38.296
Well, I was his parishioner
at St. Vincent's Church

1009
01:02:38.297 --> 01:02:40.006
about 15 years ago.

1010
01:02:40.007 --> 01:02:42.425
I hadn't seen
or heard of him for years

1011
01:02:42.426 --> 01:02:44.969
when he called me last fall.

1012
01:02:44.970 --> 01:02:47.806
He needed help, so...

1013
01:02:49.266 --> 01:02:50.601
What kind of help, doctor?

1014
01:02:51.727 --> 01:02:54.187
He wanted a medical perspective

1015
01:02:54.188 --> 01:02:55.480
from a psychiatrist,

1016
01:02:55.481 --> 01:02:59.108
you know, o-one
that he knew and trusted,

1017
01:02:59.109 --> 01:03:04.573
to observe Emily's physical and
mental state during... this...

1018
01:03:06.408 --> 01:03:08.284
During the exorcism.

1019
01:03:08.285 --> 01:03:09.662
Yeah.

1020
01:03:12.540 --> 01:03:14.709
[♪♪♪]

1021
01:03:16.877 --> 01:03:20.129
Doctor?

1022
01:03:20.130 --> 01:03:21.632
Doctor.

1023
01:03:23.217 --> 01:03:25.052
Can you help our case?

1024
01:03:27.095 --> 01:03:30.640
That girl was not schizophrenic,

1025
01:03:30.641 --> 01:03:34.060
and she was not epileptic
or any combination of the two.

1026
01:03:34.061 --> 01:03:36.145
I've seen hundreds of people
with those problems.

1027
01:03:36.146 --> 01:03:38.565
They can be terrible
afflictions, of course, but...

1028
01:03:38.566 --> 01:03:39.607
[INHALES]

1029
01:03:39.608 --> 01:03:41.234
...they don't scare me.

1030
01:03:41.235 --> 01:03:44.111
But what you saw that night
in Emily, that did scare you.

1031
01:03:44.112 --> 01:03:46.865
God, if I'd known,
I never would've been there.

1032
01:03:49.993 --> 01:03:52.913
I started praying again
since then, you know.

1033
01:03:54.956 --> 01:03:56.332
[INHALES]

1034
01:03:56.333 --> 01:03:57.917
I e-examined that girl

1035
01:03:57.918 --> 01:04:00.545
before I drove back
to the city that night.

1036
01:04:00.546 --> 01:04:02.338
She was lucid,

1037
01:04:02.339 --> 01:04:06.467
and she was completely aware of
this separate entity inside her.

1038
01:04:06.468 --> 01:04:08.386
When she wasn't in his grip,

1039
01:04:08.387 --> 01:04:10.971
she was totally herself,
completely normal.

1040
01:04:10.972 --> 01:04:14.475
And, of course, this awareness
of her alternate mental state

1041
01:04:14.476 --> 01:04:16.227
is counter-indicative
of psychosis.

1042
01:04:16.228 --> 01:04:17.978
Crazy people don't know
they're crazy.

1043
01:04:17.979 --> 01:04:19.897
That's right.

1044
01:04:19.898 --> 01:04:23.192
You'll testify to all of this
in detail?

1045
01:04:23.193 --> 01:04:25.027
Everything you saw?

1046
01:04:25.028 --> 01:04:26.237
Send me the case files,

1047
01:04:26.238 --> 01:04:28.364
and tell me when to be in court.

1048
01:04:28.365 --> 01:04:30.742
Thank you, doctor.

1049
01:04:30.743 --> 01:04:33.578
We need this.

1050
01:04:33.579 --> 01:04:37.164
Before he was arrested,
Father Moore sent this to me.

1051
01:04:37.165 --> 01:04:40.752
Asked me to take care of it.

1052
01:04:40.753 --> 01:04:42.879
That's your burden now.

1053
01:04:45.466 --> 01:04:46.591
One more thing:

1054
01:04:46.592 --> 01:04:48.593
When you saw Emily,
did Father Moore

1055
01:04:48.594 --> 01:04:50.470
ask you to give her
any medical help?

1056
01:04:50.471 --> 01:04:53.097
He was already trying to
stop her from injuring herself

1057
01:04:53.098 --> 01:04:55.767
and urging her to eat.

1058
01:04:55.768 --> 01:04:58.687
And I told him, as a doctor,
I couldn't help her.

1059
01:05:03.442 --> 01:05:04.526
<i>[LATCH CLICKS]</i>

1060
01:05:06.403 --> 01:05:08.947
Dr. Cartwright's
going to testify.

1061
01:05:14.119 --> 01:05:15.745
Don't you get it?

1062
01:05:15.746 --> 01:05:18.414
He's not just an eyewitness
to the exorcism.

1063
01:05:18.415 --> 01:05:20.667
He can also refute
the prosecution's medical case.

1064
01:05:20.668 --> 01:05:21.627
This is huge for us!

1065
01:05:21.628 --> 01:05:24.504
When do I get to testify?

1066
01:05:24.505 --> 01:05:27.006
I don't know. Look, let's just
take this one step at a time.

1067
01:05:27.007 --> 01:05:31.469
No. What matters most
is Emily's story,

1068
01:05:31.470 --> 01:05:33.472
which only I can tell.

1069
01:05:35.140 --> 01:05:36.517
I understand.

1070
01:05:38.268 --> 01:05:40.436
[CELL DOOR SLAMS IN DISTANCE]

1071
01:05:40.437 --> 01:05:42.480
Have you thought about
what I said before?

1072
01:05:42.481 --> 01:05:47.528
About dark forces
and demonic attacks?

1073
01:05:51.824 --> 01:05:53.742
Yes, I have.

1074
01:05:59.623 --> 01:06:03.125
That day,
after Briggs testified...

1075
01:06:03.126 --> 01:06:05.169
<i>[WIND WHISTLING]</i>

1076
01:06:05.170 --> 01:06:08.130
<i>...I was feeling awful.</i>

1077
01:06:08.131 --> 01:06:12.009
<i>And I went out for a walk
just to clear my head, and...</i>

1078
01:06:12.010 --> 01:06:14.554
<i>I was thinking about
what you said to me.</i>

1079
01:06:14.555 --> 01:06:19.767
<i>Thinking, "What if...
demons really do exist?"</i>

1080
01:06:19.768 --> 01:06:24.605
And wondering what that would
mean if I believed that.

1081
01:06:24.606 --> 01:06:26.273
Because...

1082
01:06:26.274 --> 01:06:30.862
God knows, I have my own demons.

1083
01:06:30.863 --> 01:06:33.365
And I saw something
lying on the sidewalk.

1084
01:06:35.283 --> 01:06:38.536
[♪♪♪]

1085
01:06:38.537 --> 01:06:40.914
<i>It was a gold locket...</i>

1086
01:06:40.915 --> 01:06:46.962
<i>with the initials E.C.B.
engraved on it.</i>

1087
01:06:47.838 --> 01:06:50.423
My middle name is Christine.

1088
01:06:50.424 --> 01:06:54.301
Erin Christine Bruner.

1089
01:06:54.302 --> 01:06:59.473
And of all the people walking by
that day, <i>I</i> found that locket.

1090
01:06:59.474 --> 01:07:02.309
What are the chances of that?

1091
01:07:02.310 --> 01:07:05.605
I-I don't know,
maybe it was a sign.

1092
01:07:05.606 --> 01:07:09.859
Or maybe it was just some
incredible coincidence.

1093
01:07:09.860 --> 01:07:12.194
But it made me feel...

1094
01:07:12.195 --> 01:07:16.657
like no matter what mistakes
I've made in the past...

1095
01:07:16.658 --> 01:07:20.661
at that moment, I was exactly
where I was meant to be.

1096
01:07:20.662 --> 01:07:22.914
Like I was on the right path.

1097
01:07:22.915 --> 01:07:24.999
Hmm.

1098
01:07:25.000 --> 01:07:28.587
You sound more like
a mystic than an agnostic.

1099
01:07:30.213 --> 01:07:32.132
Are you wearing the locket now?

1100
01:07:34.760 --> 01:07:36.136
No.

1101
01:07:37.262 --> 01:07:38.346
You should.

1102
01:07:43.727 --> 01:07:47.230
The archdiocese doesn't
want you to testify.

1103
01:07:48.899 --> 01:07:51.484
They're just afraid
that I'll embarrass them...

1104
01:07:51.485 --> 01:07:53.486
testify to some
medieval-sounding

1105
01:07:53.487 --> 01:07:54.821
supernatural nonsense.

1106
01:07:54.822 --> 01:07:58.282
They're expecting me
to talk you out of it.

1107
01:07:58.283 --> 01:08:00.869
I've just decided
I'm not even gonna try.

1108
01:08:01.578 --> 01:08:04.079
Why not?

1109
01:08:04.080 --> 01:08:07.124
If the archdiocese wants
to avoid embarrassment,

1110
01:08:07.125 --> 01:08:10.837
they need you to walk out
of here a free man.

1111
01:08:10.838 --> 01:08:13.422
I believe a jury will find you
sincere and credible,

1112
01:08:13.423 --> 01:08:16.509
<i>and</i> when Dr. Cartwright
corroborates your testimony,

1113
01:08:16.510 --> 01:08:18.845
and refutes the prosecution's
medical arguments,

1114
01:08:18.846 --> 01:08:20.055
we'll get an acquittal.

1115
01:08:21.306 --> 01:08:24.018
And everyone
will thank me for it.

1116
01:08:33.902 --> 01:08:37.031
[VOICE WHISPERS]

1117
01:08:42.995 --> 01:08:46.498
[WOMAN SCREAMING IN DISTANCE]

1118
01:08:51.753 --> 01:08:54.589
[♪♪♪]

1119
01:09:00.303 --> 01:09:05.016
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

1120
01:09:05.017 --> 01:09:06.642
WOMAN:
<i>Emily!</i>

1121
01:09:06.643 --> 01:09:09.688
<i>[SCREAMING CONTINUES]</i>

1122
01:09:15.944 --> 01:09:17.029
[SCREAMING STOPS]

1123
01:09:19.614 --> 01:09:22.325
[WHISPERS]
God help me.

1124
01:09:28.623 --> 01:09:30.958
MAN: Do you swear to
tell the truth, the whole truth,

1125
01:09:30.959 --> 01:09:32.001
so help you God?

1126
01:09:32.002 --> 01:09:32.961
I do.

1127
01:09:32.962 --> 01:09:34.587
ERIN:
<i>Father Moore,</i>

1128
01:09:34.588 --> 01:09:36.338
before you could
perform the exorcism,

1129
01:09:36.339 --> 01:09:38.257
you had to get the sanction
of the Church.

1130
01:09:38.258 --> 01:09:42.386
Yes, on October the 27th
of last year, I presented

1131
01:09:42.387 --> 01:09:45.347
my assessment and recommendation
to the archbishop,

1132
01:09:45.348 --> 01:09:47.767
and he authorized
the exorcism that day,

1133
01:09:47.768 --> 01:09:49.143
before I left his office.

1134
01:09:49.144 --> 01:09:51.395
Tell us what happened
that night.

1135
01:09:51.396 --> 01:09:53.397
I drove home.

1136
01:09:53.398 --> 01:09:56.483
I sat up till after midnight
studying <i>The Roman Ritual,</i>

1137
01:09:56.484 --> 01:09:58.111
thinking about what lay ahead.

1138
01:09:58.112 --> 01:10:00.696
You mean
<i>The Roman Ritual of Exorcism?</i>

1139
01:10:00.697 --> 01:10:02.448
A text used by Catholic priests
as a guide

1140
01:10:02.449 --> 01:10:04.366
to the performance
of the exorcism rite.

1141
01:10:04.367 --> 01:10:07.578
Yes, I think I actually fell
asleep with the book in my hand.

1142
01:10:07.579 --> 01:10:08.955
What happened next?

1143
01:10:08.956 --> 01:10:09.997
[THUNDER CRACKS]

1144
01:10:09.998 --> 01:10:11.874
MOORE:
<i>I woke up, freezing.</i>

1145
01:10:11.875 --> 01:10:13.834
<i>It was exactly 3 a.m.</i>

1146
01:10:13.835 --> 01:10:14.877
[TICKING STOPS]

1147
01:10:14.878 --> 01:10:16.253
<i>Three a.m. is</i>

1148
01:10:16.254 --> 01:10:18.005
the demonic witching hour.

1149
01:10:18.006 --> 01:10:21.508
It's a way for demons
to mock the Holy Trinity.

1150
01:10:21.509 --> 01:10:24.929
It's an inversion of 3 p.m.,
the miracle hour,

1151
01:10:24.930 --> 01:10:30.017
which is traditionally accepted
as the hour of Christ's death.

1152
01:10:30.018 --> 01:10:32.728
I thought
I smelled something burning.

1153
01:10:32.729 --> 01:10:34.354
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

1154
01:10:34.355 --> 01:10:36.398
<i>Only later did I connect it,
and I...</i>

1155
01:10:36.399 --> 01:10:39.652
<i>I remembered that that same
smell of something burning</i>

1156
01:10:39.653 --> 01:10:41.904
<i>had been perceived by Emily.</i>

1157
01:10:41.905 --> 01:10:43.781
[♪♪♪]

1158
01:10:43.782 --> 01:10:46.367
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

1159
01:11:27.868 --> 01:11:30.245
[FLOORBOARDS CREAK]

1160
01:11:31.246 --> 01:11:32.413
[THUNDER CRACKS]

1161
01:11:47.721 --> 01:11:50.098
[SHRIEKING]

1162
01:11:52.184 --> 01:11:54.476
Holy Mary, mother of God,

1163
01:11:54.477 --> 01:11:57.272
pray for us sinners, now and...

1164
01:12:00.734 --> 01:12:04.237
Pray for us sinners, now and...

1165
01:12:04.238 --> 01:12:05.947
at the hour of our...

1166
01:12:08.116 --> 01:12:09.450
[GASPS]

1167
01:12:10.410 --> 01:12:11.494
At the hour of...

1168
01:12:13.538 --> 01:12:15.331
[♪♪♪]

1169
01:12:26.927 --> 01:12:29.179
[GROANS]

1170
01:12:30.597 --> 01:12:32.515
[PANTING]

1171
01:12:42.609 --> 01:12:44.777
THOMAS: What do
you make of this gesture,

1172
01:12:44.778 --> 01:12:48.281
this nod in your direction?

1173
01:12:48.282 --> 01:12:49.656
I don't know.

1174
01:12:49.657 --> 01:12:53.619
Some kind of acknowledgment,
I guess.

1175
01:12:53.620 --> 01:12:56.331
That the game is on.

1176
01:12:57.124 --> 01:12:59.583
[SCOFFS]

1177
01:12:59.584 --> 01:13:02.419
You're really God's gunslinger,
aren't you, Father?

1178
01:13:02.420 --> 01:13:04.797
Standing tall
and facing down the devil

1179
01:13:04.798 --> 01:13:06.257
with your prayer book
at your side.

1180
01:13:06.258 --> 01:13:08.550
Objection, Your Honor.
He's harassing my witness.

1181
01:13:08.551 --> 01:13:10.136
Sustained. Mr. Thomas,

1182
01:13:10.137 --> 01:13:13.139
you know I won't allow that
in my courtroom.

1183
01:13:13.140 --> 01:13:14.933
Forgive me, Your Honor.

1184
01:13:16.893 --> 01:13:19.686
Father, did you understand
this black-robed figure

1185
01:13:19.687 --> 01:13:21.355
to be... the devil?

1186
01:13:21.356 --> 01:13:23.149
I believe it was
a demonic manifestation.

1187
01:13:23.150 --> 01:13:25.359
Like the demonic force
you believe possessed Emily?

1188
01:13:25.360 --> 01:13:27.486
Yes. Why do you think
it appeared to you?

1189
01:13:27.487 --> 01:13:30.364
I believe the demonic
can appear as an apparition,

1190
01:13:30.365 --> 01:13:33.617
much like a ghost, in an attempt
to excite our fear.

1191
01:13:33.618 --> 01:13:35.328
Did it excite your fear, Father?

1192
01:13:35.329 --> 01:13:37.163
It scared the hell outta me.

1193
01:13:37.164 --> 01:13:40.666
So this night, when you began
to prepare Emily's exorcism,

1194
01:13:40.667 --> 01:13:42.918
was it your first encounter
with this demon ghost?

1195
01:13:42.919 --> 01:13:44.003
Yes.

1196
01:13:44.004 --> 01:13:45.546
Have you seen it again?

1197
01:13:48.633 --> 01:13:50.468
I've seen it ever since.

1198
01:13:55.265 --> 01:13:57.976
THOMAS: No further
questions at this time.

1199
01:14:02.647 --> 01:14:04.774
Redirect, Your Honor.

1200
01:14:06.818 --> 01:14:09.945
Father Moore, after you received
the bishop's authorization,

1201
01:14:09.946 --> 01:14:11.655
when did you proceed
with an exorcism?

1202
01:14:11.656 --> 01:14:13.157
October 31st.

1203
01:14:13.158 --> 01:14:16.118
On Halloween.
Isn't that a bit dramatic?

1204
01:14:16.119 --> 01:14:19.372
Halloween tradition is based
on legends throughout history

1205
01:14:19.373 --> 01:14:21.540
that indicate a real increase

1206
01:14:21.541 --> 01:14:23.417
in spiritual activity
on that night,

1207
01:14:23.418 --> 01:14:25.085
and I thought we could use
the occasion

1208
01:14:25.086 --> 01:14:26.879
to draw them into the open.

1209
01:14:26.880 --> 01:14:28.881
The demons, you mean?
Yes.

1210
01:14:28.882 --> 01:14:30.842
Father Moore...

1211
01:14:32.344 --> 01:14:34.678
can you identify this?

1212
01:14:34.679 --> 01:14:36.305
It's my tape recorder.

1213
01:14:36.306 --> 01:14:38.473
I used it
to record the exorcism.

1214
01:14:38.474 --> 01:14:41.852
Inside is the tape
I made that night.

1215
01:14:41.853 --> 01:14:44.104
Why would you make such a tape?

1216
01:14:44.105 --> 01:14:46.899
Ever since the technology
has been available,

1217
01:14:46.900 --> 01:14:48.734
exorcists have used
tape recorders

1218
01:14:48.735 --> 01:14:50.152
to authenticate the ritual

1219
01:14:50.153 --> 01:14:52.529
and provide a record
for later review.

1220
01:14:52.530 --> 01:14:54.656
I offer into evidence
this recorder and audiotape

1221
01:14:54.657 --> 01:14:56.909
as Defense Exhibits A and B.
Objection, Your Honor.

1222
01:14:56.910 --> 01:14:59.119
We were not made aware
of the existence of this tape

1223
01:14:59.120 --> 01:15:01.414
until late last night.
Neither were we, Your Honor.

1224
01:15:01.415 --> 01:15:04.208
This tape is new evidence we
just received yesterday evening.

1225
01:15:04.209 --> 01:15:05.959
We have provided
counsel for the People

1226
01:15:05.960 --> 01:15:07.544
with a transcript
of its contents.

1227
01:15:07.545 --> 01:15:10.130
You mean this tape was not
given to you by your client?

1228
01:15:10.131 --> 01:15:12.925
No, Your Honor. We received it
from a reluctant witness,

1229
01:15:12.926 --> 01:15:15.052
Dr. Graham Cartwright,
who will also be called

1230
01:15:15.053 --> 01:15:16.470
to testify to its authenticity.

1231
01:15:16.471 --> 01:15:18.555
Your Honor, I...
The People will find his name

1232
01:15:18.556 --> 01:15:19.890
on the updated witness list

1233
01:15:19.891 --> 01:15:21.559
we provided to them
this morning.

1234
01:15:25.939 --> 01:15:28.233
Very well. I'll allow it
into evidence.

1235
01:15:31.319 --> 01:15:32.904
Father Moore.

1236
01:15:34.530 --> 01:15:37.742
Will you play the tape
for us now?

1237
01:15:43.164 --> 01:15:44.915
[STATIC CRACKLING]

1238
01:15:44.916 --> 01:15:48.294
MOORE [OVER TAPE]: <i>This
is the exorcism of Emily Rose.</i>

1239
01:15:48.295 --> 01:15:52.047
<i>Those present are myself,
Father Richard Moore...</i>

1240
01:15:52.048 --> 01:15:53.132
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

1241
01:15:53.133 --> 01:15:56.260
...Nathaniel, Emily's father...

1242
01:15:56.261 --> 01:16:01.056
Jason... her friend,

1243
01:16:01.057 --> 01:16:06.312
a doctor who is here to monitor
Emily during the ritual,

1244
01:16:06.313 --> 01:16:08.522
and Emily herself...

1245
01:16:08.523 --> 01:16:12.777
who has given her permission
for the ritual to be performed.

1246
01:16:14.112 --> 01:16:15.989
All right, now listen:

1247
01:16:17.615 --> 01:16:19.408
You may say the rosary

1248
01:16:19.409 --> 01:16:21.785
or any private prayer
of your own for her deliverance

1249
01:16:21.786 --> 01:16:23.788
when you're not responding
to my words.

1250
01:16:25.123 --> 01:16:27.374
Above all...

1251
01:16:27.375 --> 01:16:30.461
do whatever I ask,
without question.

1252
01:16:30.462 --> 01:16:34.589
Don't ask it any questions...

1253
01:16:34.590 --> 01:16:38.052
or pay any attention
to what it says.

1254
01:16:39.220 --> 01:16:40.804
"It"?

1255
01:16:40.805 --> 01:16:42.973
We won't be dealing
with Emily tonight.

1256
01:16:42.974 --> 01:16:46.144
[CHUCKLING]

1257
01:16:48.355 --> 01:16:51.107
MOORE:
Restrain her.

1258
01:16:52.900 --> 01:16:54.735
[EMILY PANTING]

1259
01:16:57.531 --> 01:17:01.909
MOORE: Lord Jesus
Christ, have mercy on us.

1260
01:17:10.418 --> 01:17:12.253
[PANTING STOPS]

1261
01:17:13.671 --> 01:17:17.217
[♪♪♪]

1262
01:17:23.056 --> 01:17:24.598
It has begun.

1263
01:17:24.599 --> 01:17:26.225
Let us pray.

1264
01:17:26.226 --> 01:17:28.101
[RAIN PATTERING]

1265
01:17:28.102 --> 01:17:29.187
[THUNDER CRACKS]

1266
01:17:32.982 --> 01:17:35.442
NATHANIEL & JASON: Because
she hopes in you, my God.

1267
01:17:35.443 --> 01:17:38.778
MOORE: Send her help
from the holy place, Lord.

1268
01:17:38.779 --> 01:17:40.906
NATHANIEL & JASON:
Give her heavenly protection.

1269
01:17:40.907 --> 01:17:43.450
MOORE:
May the Lord be with you.

1270
01:17:43.451 --> 01:17:45.911
NATHANIEL & JASON:
And with your spirit.

1271
01:17:45.912 --> 01:17:48.080
MOORE:
Our Father...

1272
01:17:48.081 --> 01:17:51.876
ALL: Who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name.

1273
01:17:54.379 --> 01:17:56.046
My God. Are you all right?

1274
01:17:56.047 --> 01:17:58.173
[IN GERMAN] Dolls and
kisses and crosses and wishes,

1275
01:17:58.174 --> 01:18:01.134
you think that can save
your little girl?

1276
01:18:01.135 --> 01:18:02.803
[GROWLS]

1277
01:18:04.639 --> 01:18:08.183
Thy kingdom come,
thy will be done,

1278
01:18:08.184 --> 01:18:10.561
on earth as it is in heaven.
I'm fine.

1279
01:18:10.562 --> 01:18:13.813
Give us this day
our daily bread.

1280
01:18:13.814 --> 01:18:15.815
ALL:
And forgive us our trespasses,

1281
01:18:15.816 --> 01:18:19.194
as we forgive those
that trespass against us.

1282
01:18:19.195 --> 01:18:20.695
And lead us not
into temptation...

1283
01:18:20.696 --> 01:18:26.701
[IN ENGLISH]
But deliver us from eeeeevilllll!

1284
01:18:26.702 --> 01:18:30.414
Who are you, demon?
Tell me your name.

1285
01:18:30.415 --> 01:18:32.082
[BUZZING]

1286
01:18:32.083 --> 01:18:34.751
[DOOR CREAKS]

1287
01:18:34.752 --> 01:18:36.837
[GROWLING]

1288
01:18:38.339 --> 01:18:42.134
[IN LATIN] I am the one
who dwells within...

1289
01:18:42.135 --> 01:18:44.303
[IN LATIN]
In the Name of Christ...

1290
01:18:44.304 --> 01:18:46.346
identify yourself!

1291
01:18:46.347 --> 01:18:48.432
[IN ENGLISH] One, two,
three, four, five, six.

1292
01:18:48.433 --> 01:18:50.392
One, two, three,
four, five, six.

1293
01:18:50.393 --> 01:18:51.477
Trick or treat.

1294
01:18:51.478 --> 01:18:53.562
I give you treats and tricks.

1295
01:18:53.563 --> 01:18:56.649
One, two, three,
four, five, six.

1296
01:18:56.650 --> 01:18:58.526
[CATS GROWLING]

1297
01:18:59.986 --> 01:19:01.028
[HISSES]

1298
01:19:01.946 --> 01:19:03.864
JASON:
Father Moore!

1299
01:19:14.668 --> 01:19:16.210
Papa!

1300
01:19:16.877 --> 01:19:19.172
[♪♪♪]

1301
01:19:27.430 --> 01:19:29.098
Emily!

1302
01:19:42.153 --> 01:19:44.946
NATHANIEL:
Emily!

1303
01:19:44.947 --> 01:19:47.616
She feels so hot, Father!

1304
01:19:47.617 --> 01:19:49.535
She's burning up!

1305
01:19:49.536 --> 01:19:50.995
[EMILY SHRIEKING]

1306
01:19:53.456 --> 01:19:55.541
Hold her down there
on the straw!

1307
01:19:55.542 --> 01:19:56.668
Hold her!

1308
01:20:01.839 --> 01:20:02.881
Emily!

1309
01:20:02.882 --> 01:20:04.592
[HOWLS]

1310
01:20:06.386 --> 01:20:08.887
[NEIGHING]

1311
01:20:08.888 --> 01:20:10.931
[HOWL CONTINUES]

1312
01:20:14.894 --> 01:20:16.436
[SNARLS]

1313
01:20:16.437 --> 01:20:20.775
Doctor! I need you here now.
Watch her vital signs.

1314
01:20:21.984 --> 01:20:24.361
In the beginning was the Word.

1315
01:20:24.362 --> 01:20:26.279
And the Word was with God.

1316
01:20:26.280 --> 01:20:28.699
And the word was the word.
MOORE: And the Word was God.

1317
01:20:28.700 --> 01:20:29.949
What a wonderful word it was.

1318
01:20:29.950 --> 01:20:31.493
Through him,
all things were made.

1319
01:20:31.494 --> 01:20:33.705
Without him, nothing was made
that has been made.

1320
01:20:36.290 --> 01:20:39.501
And the 70 disciples
returned again with joy, saying,

1321
01:20:39.502 --> 01:20:42.504
"Lord, even the devils
are subject unto us

1322
01:20:42.505 --> 01:20:43.672
through thy name."

1323
01:20:43.673 --> 01:20:45.257
CARTWRIGHT:
Her heart is racing.

1324
01:20:45.258 --> 01:20:46.800
It's almost 180 beats a minute.

1325
01:20:46.801 --> 01:20:50.845
I beheld Satan as lightning
falls from heaven.

1326
01:20:50.846 --> 01:20:56.351
Behold! I give you power to
tread on serpents and scorpions,

1327
01:20:56.352 --> 01:20:58.520
and over all the power
of the enemy.

1328
01:20:58.521 --> 01:21:01.523
And nothing shall,
by any means, hurt you.

1329
01:21:01.524 --> 01:21:03.484
[IN GREEK]
Nothing...?

1330
01:21:04.402 --> 01:21:05.820
Ah!

1331
01:21:12.285 --> 01:21:13.453
[EMILY MOANING]

1332
01:21:15.413 --> 01:21:17.331
[SIZZLING, EMILY SCREAMING]

1333
01:21:31.971 --> 01:21:33.930
Release him, demon.

1334
01:21:33.931 --> 01:21:37.810
I command you, in the name
of our Lord, Jesus Christ.

1335
01:21:37.811 --> 01:21:40.104
[SCREAMS]

1336
01:21:41.481 --> 01:21:43.231
Tell me your name, wicked one.

1337
01:21:43.232 --> 01:21:45.317
[IN LATIN] One, two,
three, four, five, six!

1338
01:21:45.318 --> 01:21:48.403
He who commands you is he
who ordered you thrown down

1339
01:21:48.404 --> 01:21:50.864
from the highest heaven
into the depths of hell.

1340
01:21:50.865 --> 01:21:53.826
In the name of our Lord,
Jesus Christ,

1341
01:21:53.827 --> 01:21:55.828
I now command you:

1342
01:21:55.829 --> 01:21:57.871
Give me your name, demon!

1343
01:21:57.872 --> 01:22:00.040
[IN ENGLISH]
Naaaaaames!

1344
01:22:01.626 --> 01:22:03.837
Naaaaaames!

1345
01:22:05.087 --> 01:22:10.801
[IN ARAMAIC] One, two,
three, four, five, six!

1346
01:22:10.802 --> 01:22:13.428
Ancient serpents.

1347
01:22:13.429 --> 01:22:16.390
Depart from this servant of God!

1348
01:22:17.809 --> 01:22:21.520
Tell me your six names!

1349
01:22:21.521 --> 01:22:25.774
[IN ENGLISH] We are
the ones who dwell within.

1350
01:22:25.775 --> 01:22:29.235
[IN HEBREW] I am the one
who dwelt within Cain!

1351
01:22:29.236 --> 01:22:32.739
[IN LATIN] I am the one
who dwelt within Nero!

1352
01:22:32.740 --> 01:22:36.242
[IN GREEK]
I once dwelt within Judas!

1353
01:22:36.243 --> 01:22:37.744
[IN GERMAN]
And I was with Legion!

1354
01:22:37.745 --> 01:22:40.832
[IN ARAMAIC]
I am Belial!

1355
01:22:41.332 --> 01:22:42.749
[HISSES]

1356
01:22:42.750 --> 01:22:45.460
[IN ENGLISH]
And I am Lucifer...

1357
01:22:45.461 --> 01:22:48.506
the devil in the flesh.

1358
01:22:54.428 --> 01:22:57.598
[UNEARTHLY HOWL]

1359
01:23:03.688 --> 01:23:05.188
Mr. Rose!

1360
01:23:05.189 --> 01:23:07.066
Doctor, help him!

1361
01:23:25.000 --> 01:23:27.753
MOORE: <i>After a few
moments, Mr. Rose revived.</i>

1362
01:23:27.754 --> 01:23:30.923
<i>The exorcism
had to be abandoned.</i>

1363
01:23:30.924 --> 01:23:36.219
Emily was taken to her room
and soon fell into a deep sleep.

1364
01:23:36.220 --> 01:23:39.723
The whole thing
was a complete failure.

1365
01:23:39.724 --> 01:23:41.474
Describe her behavior

1366
01:23:41.475 --> 01:23:43.142
from the night
of the failed exorcism

1367
01:23:43.143 --> 01:23:44.394
until the time of her death.

1368
01:23:44.395 --> 01:23:45.562
Oh...

1369
01:23:45.563 --> 01:23:47.647
Violence towards others
and herself,

1370
01:23:47.648 --> 01:23:50.650
sometimes she'd scream
for hours on end.

1371
01:23:50.651 --> 01:23:52.945
She drove her head
through windows,

1372
01:23:52.946 --> 01:23:55.614
tried to bite... Tried to bite
holes in the walls,

1373
01:23:55.615 --> 01:23:57.156
breaking several more
of her teeth,

1374
01:23:57.157 --> 01:24:00.034
as you saw in the...
In the postmortem photograph.

1375
01:24:00.035 --> 01:24:01.411
You witnessed this?

1376
01:24:01.412 --> 01:24:03.872
Some of it, yes, I...
I tried to visit every day

1377
01:24:03.873 --> 01:24:06.875
and, uh... the family
told me the rest.

1378
01:24:06.876 --> 01:24:08.710
Did you attempt
another exorcism?

1379
01:24:08.711 --> 01:24:11.630
I wanted to, but Emily refused.

1380
01:24:11.631 --> 01:24:14.340
And without the consent
of the possessed,

1381
01:24:14.341 --> 01:24:16.760
the exorcism ritual
can't be performed.

1382
01:24:16.761 --> 01:24:18.887
Did you encourage her to eat?

1383
01:24:18.888 --> 01:24:23.099
Yes, every time I saw her,
but the few times she tried,

1384
01:24:23.100 --> 01:24:24.726
it seemed like...

1385
01:24:24.727 --> 01:24:28.313
Seemed like she couldn't swallow
or she couldn't keep it down.

1386
01:24:28.314 --> 01:24:29.648
What about medical care?

1387
01:24:29.649 --> 01:24:31.024
I wanted her to continue.

1388
01:24:31.025 --> 01:24:33.026
I never said she should quit
seeing her doctors.

1389
01:24:33.027 --> 01:24:34.193
That would have been
quite wrong.

1390
01:24:34.194 --> 01:24:35.779
Medical care is not my field.

1391
01:24:35.780 --> 01:24:39.283
But you did suggest she stop
taking the drug, Gambutrol.

1392
01:24:42.161 --> 01:24:43.579
Yes.

1393
01:24:46.373 --> 01:24:50.251
After the exorcism,
she asked for my counsel.

1394
01:24:50.252 --> 01:24:52.754
She told me that the drugs
had never helped her.

1395
01:24:52.755 --> 01:24:55.966
After all, she was on Gambutrol
during the exorcism

1396
01:24:55.967 --> 01:24:58.301
when her so-called symptoms
were at their peak.

1397
01:24:58.302 --> 01:25:03.849
Ultimately, we both felt that
she was beyond medical care,

1398
01:25:03.850 --> 01:25:08.687
and that she had to see
this through to the end...

1399
01:25:08.688 --> 01:25:10.773
by faith alone.

1400
01:25:15.152 --> 01:25:19.698
The dual voices
we just heard on this tape...

1401
01:25:19.699 --> 01:25:22.993
you're certain that they
were both coming from Emily

1402
01:25:22.994 --> 01:25:24.369
at the same time?

1403
01:25:24.370 --> 01:25:25.745
Yes. Yes, I heard them.

1404
01:25:25.746 --> 01:25:28.540
Have you tampered
with this tape in any way?

1405
01:25:28.541 --> 01:25:30.584
No. No, I have not.

1406
01:25:32.003 --> 01:25:34.296
No further questions
at this time.

1407
01:25:38.968 --> 01:25:40.594
Mr. Thomas?

1408
01:25:44.139 --> 01:25:46.516
Father Moore,
do you consider this tape

1409
01:25:46.517 --> 01:25:48.518
to be proof of the supernatural?

1410
01:25:48.519 --> 01:25:53.356
I think it's a record
of certain... indications

1411
01:25:53.357 --> 01:25:55.358
that Emily was possessed, uh...

1412
01:25:55.359 --> 01:25:56.860
Signs of possession,
you may call them.

1413
01:25:56.861 --> 01:25:58.152
By "signs of possession"

1414
01:25:58.153 --> 01:26:00.572
would you mean
her speaking in languages

1415
01:26:00.573 --> 01:26:02.615
we might assume
she couldn't possibly know?

1416
01:26:02.616 --> 01:26:05.994
And the vocalization of two
distinct voices simultaneously?

1417
01:26:05.995 --> 01:26:08.204
Yes. Among other signs
that I observed

1418
01:26:08.205 --> 01:26:10.582
and described to the court
while the tape was playing.

1419
01:26:10.583 --> 01:26:12.834
Things I saw. Things you can't
really hear on the tape.

1420
01:26:12.835 --> 01:26:15.545
But we'll just have to take you
at your word on those, won't we?

1421
01:26:15.546 --> 01:26:17.296
Your Honor.
Mr. Thomas.

1422
01:26:17.297 --> 01:26:20.759
I apologize. Father,
as Emily's parish priest,

1423
01:26:20.760 --> 01:26:23.762
are you aware that she underwent
advanced catechism training?

1424
01:26:23.763 --> 01:26:25.097
Yes. Yes.
Her family is very devout.

1425
01:26:25.098 --> 01:26:26.514
And in that training,

1426
01:26:26.515 --> 01:26:28.391
did she study Ancient Greek,
Hebrew and Latin?

1427
01:26:28.392 --> 01:26:29.976
Yes, I think that's right.

1428
01:26:29.977 --> 01:26:32.478
She might have even spent
some time studying Aramaic,

1429
01:26:32.479 --> 01:26:34.230
the language of Christ
and his disciples,

1430
01:26:34.231 --> 01:26:35.941
which, according
to the transcripts,

1431
01:26:35.942 --> 01:26:37.776
we also heard
on the audiotape, correct?

1432
01:26:37.777 --> 01:26:39.193
She spoke Aramaic on the tape,

1433
01:26:39.194 --> 01:26:40.820
but I don't think
it was part of her training.

1434
01:26:40.821 --> 01:26:42.072
But it was offered

1435
01:26:42.073 --> 01:26:43.865
as an elective
at her catechism school.

1436
01:26:43.866 --> 01:26:46.492
I have the school's curriculum
here in my file if you'd like.

1437
01:26:46.493 --> 01:26:49.287
No, I... I'll accept
that she might have been

1438
01:26:49.288 --> 01:26:50.663
exposed to that language.

1439
01:26:50.664 --> 01:26:52.457
And according to
her high school records,

1440
01:26:52.458 --> 01:26:54.918
German was the foreign language
she studied there, yes?

1441
01:26:54.919 --> 01:26:56.544
I don't know.
If you say so.

1442
01:26:56.545 --> 01:26:59.005
So that pretty much covers
all the strange languages

1443
01:26:59.006 --> 01:27:00.423
we heard on the tape, correct?

1444
01:27:00.424 --> 01:27:02.176
Did I miss any?

1445
01:27:03.719 --> 01:27:05.470
No.
Good. Now, Father,

1446
01:27:05.471 --> 01:27:07.889
we've already established
that you're no medical expert.

1447
01:27:07.890 --> 01:27:09.474
As you said,
that's not your field.

1448
01:27:09.475 --> 01:27:11.893
But are you aware
of the dual sets of vocal cords

1449
01:27:11.894 --> 01:27:13.311
that every human possesses?

1450
01:27:13.312 --> 01:27:14.854
No.
Have you heard

1451
01:27:14.855 --> 01:27:17.149
of the superior vocal cords
which are a bit higher

1452
01:27:17.150 --> 01:27:19.358
than the primary ones
we use to speak?

1453
01:27:19.359 --> 01:27:20.610
No.
No, so you didn't know

1454
01:27:20.611 --> 01:27:22.236
that Tibetan monks, for example,

1455
01:27:22.237 --> 01:27:23.905
as part of their
religious training

1456
01:27:23.906 --> 01:27:26.116
actually teach themselves
to activate

1457
01:27:26.117 --> 01:27:28.827
both sets of vocal cords
at once?

1458
01:27:28.828 --> 01:27:30.620
No, I-I didn't know that.

1459
01:27:30.621 --> 01:27:32.246
Well, now that you do know,

1460
01:27:32.247 --> 01:27:33.873
would you think
it's possible that Emily,

1461
01:27:33.874 --> 01:27:35.500
in her psychotic state,

1462
01:27:35.501 --> 01:27:37.961
might have activated both
of her sets of vocal cords,

1463
01:27:37.962 --> 01:27:39.796
so as to achieve
the... amazing effect

1464
01:27:39.797 --> 01:27:41.547
we heard captured
on your audiotape?

1465
01:27:41.548 --> 01:27:43.257
Her state was not psychotic.

1466
01:27:43.258 --> 01:27:45.760
Father Moore, you told us that
in the exorcism we just heard,

1467
01:27:45.761 --> 01:27:49.597
you actually saw, once again,
this black-robed figure

1468
01:27:49.598 --> 01:27:51.016
or demonic apparition,
am I right?

1469
01:27:51.017 --> 01:27:52.225
Yes.

1470
01:27:52.226 --> 01:27:53.852
But, of course,
we couldn't see him

1471
01:27:53.853 --> 01:27:55.394
when you played the tape,
correct?

1472
01:27:55.395 --> 01:27:56.938
No, of course not.
No, of course not.

1473
01:27:56.939 --> 01:27:59.273
So that would be
yet another supernatural aspect

1474
01:27:59.274 --> 01:28:02.360
of the exorcism that your tape
doesn't prove, correct?

1475
01:28:02.361 --> 01:28:03.486
Yes.

1476
01:28:03.487 --> 01:28:06.198
Where is your dark figure,
Father?

1477
01:28:06.199 --> 01:28:08.741
Is he here now? Do I look
like your demon ghost?

1478
01:28:08.742 --> 01:28:10.911
Your Honor.
Counselor.

1479
01:28:14.456 --> 01:28:16.250
I have nothing further.

1480
01:28:17.334 --> 01:28:19.460
Does the defense wish
to redirect?

1481
01:28:19.461 --> 01:28:21.129
No, Your Honor,
but we reserve the right

1482
01:28:21.130 --> 01:28:23.089
to recall the witness
at a later time.

1483
01:28:23.090 --> 01:28:25.009
Very well.
The witness may step down.

1484
01:28:32.683 --> 01:28:35.518
Your Honor, my next witness
must have been detained.

1485
01:28:35.519 --> 01:28:37.229
If we could take a short recess,

1486
01:28:37.230 --> 01:28:38.563
so I could...

1487
01:28:38.564 --> 01:28:40.982
You've made this court
wait before, counselor.

1488
01:28:40.983 --> 01:28:43.568
I'm inclined to contin...
Your Honor, please.

1489
01:28:43.569 --> 01:28:46.445
Dr. Cartwright came to us
in good conscience.

1490
01:28:46.446 --> 01:28:49.532
As an eyewitness to the exorcism
on Father Moore's tape,

1491
01:28:49.533 --> 01:28:52.994
he can substantiate
all of my client's testimony.

1492
01:28:52.995 --> 01:28:55.038
Your Honor, the defense
has already presented

1493
01:28:55.039 --> 01:28:57.373
its exorcism testimony
in dramatic fashion.

1494
01:28:57.374 --> 01:28:59.126
Do we really have to...?

1495
01:29:05.382 --> 01:29:09.010
We have absorbed some
extraordinary testimony today.

1496
01:29:09.011 --> 01:29:11.470
I think we'll take
some time to consider it.

1497
01:29:11.471 --> 01:29:14.015
Court is adjourned
until 9:30 tomorrow morning.

1498
01:29:14.016 --> 01:29:15.059
[GAVEL CRACKS]

1499
01:29:16.977 --> 01:29:18.811
What do you mean
you can't find him?

1500
01:29:18.812 --> 01:29:20.396
I went to meet him,
and he didn't show.

1501
01:29:20.397 --> 01:29:22.148
I called his office,
I called his house.

1502
01:29:22.149 --> 01:29:23.900
[SIGHS]
Okay.

1503
01:29:23.901 --> 01:29:25.568
Go to the hospital, ask around.

1504
01:29:25.569 --> 01:29:27.280
Somebody's gotta know
where he is.

1505
01:29:28.072 --> 01:29:30.741
[♪♪♪]

1506
01:29:40.126 --> 01:29:41.627
What the hell happened?

1507
01:29:43.003 --> 01:29:45.630
Tell Father Moore I'm sorry.

1508
01:29:45.631 --> 01:29:48.300
Tell him... I know
the demons are real,

1509
01:29:48.301 --> 01:29:49.926
and I admire his courage

1510
01:29:49.927 --> 01:29:52.011
for standing and speaking
against them.

1511
01:29:52.012 --> 01:29:54.348
Tell him I know
what they can do.

1512
01:30:02.815 --> 01:30:04.191
[TIRES SCREECH]

1513
01:30:17.621 --> 01:30:18.746
Cartwright's dead.

1514
01:30:18.747 --> 01:30:20.415
I heard.

1515
01:30:21.458 --> 01:30:22.668
Are you drunk?

1516
01:30:24.670 --> 01:30:27.255
Not yet, but I'm workin' on it.

1517
01:30:27.256 --> 01:30:28.465
Have you seen this?

1518
01:30:33.512 --> 01:30:35.805
What the hell were
you thinking? Karl...

1519
01:30:35.806 --> 01:30:38.308
You told me you'd talk him
out of testifying.

1520
01:30:38.309 --> 01:30:40.852
Instead, you put on a freak show
with tape-recorded demons

1521
01:30:40.853 --> 01:30:42.687
and a dead girl
speaking in tongues,

1522
01:30:42.688 --> 01:30:44.147
<i>and</i> your client testifies

1523
01:30:44.148 --> 01:30:46.440
that the archbishop
sanctioned the exorcism.

1524
01:30:46.441 --> 01:30:47.984
We'll be lucky
if the archdiocese

1525
01:30:47.985 --> 01:30:49.777
isn't named
in additional charges.

1526
01:30:49.778 --> 01:30:51.946
I had a doctor
who was gonna corroborate.

1527
01:30:51.947 --> 01:30:53.406
Besides that,

1528
01:30:53.407 --> 01:30:55.658
Father Moore's testimony's
crucial to his defense.

1529
01:30:55.659 --> 01:30:57.451
Have you forgotten
that the archdiocese

1530
01:30:57.452 --> 01:31:00.414
is paying for this defense?
The archdiocese isn't on trial.

1531
01:31:01.999 --> 01:31:04.625
I swore an oath to do
what's best for my client.

1532
01:31:04.626 --> 01:31:07.003
Spare me the law school
pieties, Bruner.

1533
01:31:07.004 --> 01:31:09.297
You cashed in your conscience
at the door.

1534
01:31:09.298 --> 01:31:10.340
People can change.

1535
01:31:10.341 --> 01:31:12.385
Like James Van Hopper?

1536
01:31:15.762 --> 01:31:17.972
It's not over.

1537
01:31:17.973 --> 01:31:19.974
I can put Mr. Rose
on the stand

1538
01:31:19.975 --> 01:31:22.268
to corroborate Father Moore
about the exorcism.

1539
01:31:22.269 --> 01:31:23.561
And... and there are the girls.

1540
01:31:23.562 --> 01:31:25.271
Her sister, Alice,
she saw part of it.

1541
01:31:25.272 --> 01:31:27.023
They all look
like superstitious rubes.

1542
01:31:27.024 --> 01:31:28.400
They've got no credibility.

1543
01:31:28.401 --> 01:31:29.984
Ethan Thomas will
rip them to pieces.

1544
01:31:29.985 --> 01:31:31.652
You'll be worse off
than you are now,

1545
01:31:31.653 --> 01:31:33.905
if that's possible.

1546
01:31:33.906 --> 01:31:35.656
You're gonna replace me
on this case?

1547
01:31:35.657 --> 01:31:38.451
You've screwed it up
beyond all repair.

1548
01:31:38.452 --> 01:31:41.746
But the archdiocese feels
that replacing you now

1549
01:31:41.747 --> 01:31:44.498
would only draw more unnecessary
attention to the trial.

1550
01:31:44.499 --> 01:31:46.334
But just so we're clear, Bruner,

1551
01:31:46.335 --> 01:31:49.295
if you put that priest
on the stand again,

1552
01:31:49.296 --> 01:31:51.298
I will fire you.

1553
01:32:09.983 --> 01:32:11.444
[LOCK CLICKS]

1554
01:32:18.367 --> 01:32:19.910
You've been crying.

1555
01:32:23.038 --> 01:32:24.789
Dr. Cartwright is dead.

1556
01:32:24.790 --> 01:32:26.459
What?

1557
01:32:27.209 --> 01:32:28.542
He was killed.

1558
01:32:28.543 --> 01:32:31.671
There was an accident.
I'm sorry.

1559
01:32:34.425 --> 01:32:36.093
I know he was your friend.

1560
01:32:40.473 --> 01:32:42.182
We've lost.

1561
01:32:44.226 --> 01:32:46.728
Without his testimony,
it's over.

1562
01:32:47.980 --> 01:32:49.855
No.

1563
01:32:49.856 --> 01:32:51.857
No, no, no, it isn't over.

1564
01:32:51.858 --> 01:32:54.026
We're telling Emily's story.
That's what matters.

1565
01:32:54.027 --> 01:32:55.194
It can't be worth all this.

1566
01:32:55.195 --> 01:32:56.570
Yes! Yes, it is worth it.

1567
01:32:56.571 --> 01:32:58.781
Just let me go back on
the stand I can't do that.

1568
01:32:58.782 --> 01:33:00.783
And tell the rest of the story,
then you'll know.

1569
01:33:00.784 --> 01:33:02.535
I can't do that.
You must!

1570
01:33:02.536 --> 01:33:03.912
You must.

1571
01:33:09.460 --> 01:33:11.419
Erin...

1572
01:33:11.420 --> 01:33:15.840
you once said that you felt
you were on the right path.

1573
01:33:15.841 --> 01:33:18.677
Don't stray from that path.

1574
01:33:20.053 --> 01:33:21.804
Here, take this.

1575
01:33:21.805 --> 01:33:24.432
What is this?
Just read it.

1576
01:33:24.433 --> 01:33:27.978
And then... decide
what you wanna do.

1577
01:33:29.313 --> 01:33:31.105
MOORE:
<i>I saw your eyes today in court</i>

1578
01:33:31.106 --> 01:33:34.859
<i>when I explained
the significance of 3 a.m.</i>

1579
01:33:34.860 --> 01:33:37.611
<i>It's not going to stop</i>

1580
01:33:37.612 --> 01:33:40.906
<i>until Emily's story is told.</i>

1581
01:33:40.907 --> 01:33:42.826
[♪♪♪]

1582
01:34:18.111 --> 01:34:20.530
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1583
01:34:20.531 --> 01:34:22.532
Comments?

1584
01:34:22.533 --> 01:34:25.451
Are you gonna make a statement?

1585
01:34:25.452 --> 01:34:27.995
REPORTER: Do you
believe it was the devil, Erin?

1586
01:34:27.996 --> 01:34:29.872
REPORTER 2: Did you
witness the accident?

1587
01:34:29.873 --> 01:34:31.791
REPORTER 3:
Who are the other witnesses?

1588
01:34:40.342 --> 01:34:43.094
JUDGE:
Is the defense ready to proceed?

1589
01:34:43.095 --> 01:34:44.554
Yes, Your Honor.

1590
01:34:44.555 --> 01:34:47.307
The defense recalls
Father Richard Moore.

1591
01:34:54.398 --> 01:34:58.234
JUDGE: The witness is
reminded that he is still under oath.

1592
01:34:58.235 --> 01:34:59.486
[DOOR CLOSES HEAVILY]

1593
01:35:07.286 --> 01:35:09.287
When did you last see
Emily alive?

1594
01:35:09.288 --> 01:35:10.704
The night before she died.

1595
01:35:10.705 --> 01:35:12.373
Her, uh, mother,
Maria, called me

1596
01:35:12.374 --> 01:35:13.999
and said that Emily
had asked for me.

1597
01:35:14.000 --> 01:35:15.334
Why did she ask to see you?

1598
01:35:15.335 --> 01:35:16.835
To give me this.

1599
01:35:16.836 --> 01:35:19.672
Did Emily explain to you
the letter's significance?

1600
01:35:19.673 --> 01:35:22.049
Yes. She said she'd written it

1601
01:35:22.050 --> 01:35:25.219
the morning after
the failed exorcism and that...

1602
01:35:25.220 --> 01:35:27.931
That it was important
for me to share.

1603
01:35:31.726 --> 01:35:34.771
Father Moore, was...
Emily a good person?

1604
01:35:36.148 --> 01:35:38.441
I believe that one day,

1605
01:35:38.442 --> 01:35:41.320
Emily will be recognized
as a saint.

1606
01:35:42.488 --> 01:35:43.655
So she loved God.

1607
01:35:43.656 --> 01:35:45.490
Yes. She was very devout.

1608
01:35:45.491 --> 01:35:48.200
Father Moore,
if Emily loved God,

1609
01:35:48.201 --> 01:35:50.244
if she was so good
and so devout,

1610
01:35:50.245 --> 01:35:52.163
why do you think God allowed
this to happen?

1611
01:35:52.164 --> 01:35:54.248
Objection. What can
possibly be the relevance?

1612
01:35:54.249 --> 01:35:56.167
Your Honor.
It's sheer speculation.

1613
01:35:56.168 --> 01:35:58.336
Father Moore's belief
in this matter is crucial

1614
01:35:58.337 --> 01:36:01.172
in establishing his and Emily's
understanding of her condition.

1615
01:36:01.173 --> 01:36:03.882
And that mutual understanding
is paramount in determining

1616
01:36:03.883 --> 01:36:06.386
whether Father Moore was,
in fact, negligent.

1617
01:36:08.805 --> 01:36:10.348
I'm going to allow it.
Your Honor,

1618
01:36:10.349 --> 01:36:12.266
you're not really gonna
let someone testify

1619
01:36:12.267 --> 01:36:14.185
in a court of law about
why... God would allow

1620
01:36:14.186 --> 01:36:16.729
the death of a young girl.
His state of mind is critical.

1621
01:36:16.730 --> 01:36:18.523
The objection
has been overruled.

1622
01:36:18.524 --> 01:36:20.150
Again, Father Moore...

1623
01:36:22.235 --> 01:36:25.697
...why did God allow Emily
to become possessed by demons

1624
01:36:25.698 --> 01:36:27.031
and then die?

1625
01:36:27.032 --> 01:36:29.743
I can let Emily answer that.

1626
01:36:33.997 --> 01:36:37.208
"Last night, on Allhallows' Eve,

1627
01:36:37.209 --> 01:36:42.338
"Father Moore tried to cast
six demons from my body.

1628
01:36:42.339 --> 01:36:45.383
"They refused to go.

1629
01:36:45.384 --> 01:36:48.093
"After the attempted exorcism,

1630
01:36:48.094 --> 01:36:50.012
<i>I was taken to my room..."</i>

1631
01:36:50.013 --> 01:36:52.641
EMILY: <i>...and I fell
into a deep sleep.</i>

1632
01:36:54.685 --> 01:36:56.519
<i>I awoke a few hours later,</i>

1633
01:36:56.520 --> 01:36:59.939
<i>hearing a voice
calling out my name.</i>

1634
01:37:04.194 --> 01:37:07.280
[♪♪♪]

1635
01:37:59.958 --> 01:38:04.462
MOORE: <i>"Again, I heard
a voice calling my name.</i>

1636
01:38:04.463 --> 01:38:08.299
"It was the Blessed
Holy Mother of God.

1637
01:38:08.300 --> 01:38:10.968
"And when I looked at her,

1638
01:38:10.969 --> 01:38:13.011
"she smiled at me

1639
01:38:13.012 --> 01:38:15.055
"and said,

1640
01:38:15.056 --> 01:38:18.350
'Emily, heaven is not blind
to your pain.'"

1641
01:38:18.351 --> 01:38:20.603
ERIN: She said the
Virgin Mary spoke to her

1642
01:38:20.604 --> 01:38:22.104
in the middle of a field?

1643
01:38:22.105 --> 01:38:23.481
Yes.

1644
01:38:23.482 --> 01:38:25.065
And do you believe her?

1645
01:38:25.066 --> 01:38:27.193
I... I believe
Emily spoke the truth.

1646
01:38:28.612 --> 01:38:30.196
Please, continue.

1647
01:38:32.449 --> 01:38:37.328
MOORE: <i>"I asked the Blessed
Mother, 'Why do I suffer like this?'"</i>

1648
01:38:37.329 --> 01:38:41.915
Why did the demons
not leave me tonight?

1649
01:38:41.916 --> 01:38:43.793
<i>"She said, 'I am sorry, Emily.</i>

1650
01:38:43.794 --> 01:38:45.294
[DISTORTED HOWL]

1651
01:38:45.295 --> 01:38:49.006
<i>"The demons are going
to stay where they are.'</i>

1652
01:38:49.007 --> 01:38:52.760
<i>"Then she said, 'You can
come with me in peace,</i>

1653
01:38:52.761 --> 01:38:55.971
<i>"'freed of your bodily form,</i>

1654
01:38:55.972 --> 01:39:00.518
<i>"'or you can choose
to continue this.</i>

1655
01:39:00.519 --> 01:39:02.645
<i>"'You will suffer greatly.</i>

1656
01:39:02.646 --> 01:39:05.981
<i>"'But through you,
many will come to see</i>

1657
01:39:05.982 --> 01:39:08.694
<i>"'that the realm
of the spirit is real.</i>

1658
01:39:10.529 --> 01:39:13.657
<i>The choice is yours.'"</i>

1659
01:39:21.080 --> 01:39:23.624
[WHISPERING]
I choose to stay.

1660
01:39:23.625 --> 01:39:26.711
[UNEARTHLY RUMBLING & WHOOSH]

1661
01:39:26.712 --> 01:39:29.255
[♪♪♪]

1662
01:39:53.029 --> 01:39:55.197
<i>"In the end,</i>

1663
01:39:55.198 --> 01:39:58.033
"good will triumph over evil.

1664
01:39:58.034 --> 01:40:00.619
"Through my experience

1665
01:40:00.620 --> 01:40:03.790
"people will know
that demons are real.

1666
01:40:05.834 --> 01:40:08.126
"People say...

1667
01:40:08.127 --> 01:40:11.714
"that God is dead.

1668
01:40:11.715 --> 01:40:12.715
[SNIFFLES]

1669
01:40:12.716 --> 01:40:15.384
"But how can they think that

1670
01:40:15.385 --> 01:40:17.763
if I show them the devil?"

1671
01:40:20.724 --> 01:40:21.975
[SNIFFLES]

1672
01:40:23.184 --> 01:40:24.894
ERIN:
Did you see these wounds

1673
01:40:24.895 --> 01:40:27.229
on both of Emily's hands
and both feet?

1674
01:40:27.230 --> 01:40:28.564
Yes.

1675
01:40:28.565 --> 01:40:32.401
Yes, the wounds...
lasted for some time.

1676
01:40:32.402 --> 01:40:35.237
And did you attach
any supernatural significance

1677
01:40:35.238 --> 01:40:36.781
to these wounds?

1678
01:40:36.782 --> 01:40:38.073
I believe...

1679
01:40:38.074 --> 01:40:39.074
[SNIFFLES]

1680
01:40:39.075 --> 01:40:41.076
...they were stigmata.

1681
01:40:41.077 --> 01:40:44.288
By that you mean supernatural
injuries that correspond

1682
01:40:44.289 --> 01:40:46.457
to the crucifixion wounds
of Jesus Christ?

1683
01:40:46.458 --> 01:40:47.750
Yes.

1684
01:40:47.751 --> 01:40:49.334
Uh...

1685
01:40:49.335 --> 01:40:50.628
Stigmata are a...

1686
01:40:50.629 --> 01:40:53.465
Are a sign,
a mark indicating one is...

1687
01:40:54.215 --> 01:40:55.675
touched by God.

1688
01:40:59.304 --> 01:41:01.054
After that night,

1689
01:41:01.055 --> 01:41:05.058
why do you think Emily
refused another exorcism?

1690
01:41:05.059 --> 01:41:08.688
I believe sh-sh-she'd
accepted her fate.

1691
01:41:10.273 --> 01:41:11.941
[WHISPERING]
Is there anything else

1692
01:41:11.942 --> 01:41:14.027
you'd like to say about Emily?

1693
01:41:17.906 --> 01:41:18.991
No.

1694
01:41:22.619 --> 01:41:25.163
The defense rests.

1695
01:41:33.254 --> 01:41:35.923
Father Moore attaches
divine significance

1696
01:41:35.924 --> 01:41:39.635
to the wounds on Emily's
hands and feet.

1697
01:41:39.636 --> 01:41:41.054
Why?

1698
01:41:42.597 --> 01:41:44.431
Because he sees them
as confirmation

1699
01:41:44.432 --> 01:41:47.685
of what he wants to believe,

1700
01:41:47.686 --> 01:41:51.063
that Emily was a saint,
touched by the hand of God.

1701
01:41:51.064 --> 01:41:55.776
I'm afraid the truth
is far less inspiring.

1702
01:41:55.777 --> 01:41:57.653
Because the truth is,

1703
01:41:57.654 --> 01:42:01.740
by the time these "miraculous"
wounds appeared

1704
01:42:01.741 --> 01:42:05.118
Emily had already shown
a tendency to injure herself

1705
01:42:05.119 --> 01:42:06.912
and simply did so again

1706
01:42:06.913 --> 01:42:08.330
on one of the barbed wire fences

1707
01:42:08.331 --> 01:42:12.502
<i>surrounding
the Rose family farm.</i>

1708
01:42:16.506 --> 01:42:18.007
Father Moore's beliefs

1709
01:42:18.008 --> 01:42:23.178
are based on archaic
and irrational superstition.

1710
01:42:23.179 --> 01:42:26.432
Emily suffered
because she was sick...

1711
01:42:27.684 --> 01:42:29.602
not because she was a saint.

1712
01:42:31.646 --> 01:42:33.230
I'm a man of faith,

1713
01:42:33.231 --> 01:42:35.524
and I am also a man of facts.

1714
01:42:35.525 --> 01:42:37.693
And in here,

1715
01:42:37.694 --> 01:42:42.907
facts are what must matter.

1716
01:42:42.908 --> 01:42:45.534
And these are the facts
of this case:

1717
01:42:45.535 --> 01:42:50.622
Emily Rose had epilepsy,
which caused psychosis,

1718
01:42:50.623 --> 01:42:54.543
and, given time,
medicine would have cured her.

1719
01:42:54.544 --> 01:42:55.878
But it didn't. Why?

1720
01:42:55.879 --> 01:42:57.504
Because Father Richard Moore

1721
01:42:57.505 --> 01:43:01.550
convinced Emily
that she wasn't ill,

1722
01:43:01.551 --> 01:43:03.802
that she didn't need medicine.

1723
01:43:03.803 --> 01:43:06.764
And in the weeks
leading up to her death,

1724
01:43:06.765 --> 01:43:11.476
when she was clearly
in need of medical treatment,

1725
01:43:11.477 --> 01:43:14.106
he failed to have
her hospitalized.

1726
01:43:22.488 --> 01:43:23.656
So...

1727
01:43:25.033 --> 01:43:27.200
the defense has given us

1728
01:43:27.201 --> 01:43:31.204
an extraordinary,
creative explanation

1729
01:43:31.205 --> 01:43:33.707
for the events that led to this.

1730
01:43:33.708 --> 01:43:35.417
Ladies and gentlemen,

1731
01:43:35.418 --> 01:43:40.547
don't you believe it.

1732
01:43:40.548 --> 01:43:42.049
Because the fact is,

1733
01:43:42.050 --> 01:43:45.762
it wasn't the devil
that did this to Emily Rose.

1734
01:43:49.599 --> 01:43:51.350
It was the defendant.

1735
01:44:12.080 --> 01:44:13.165
Counselor.

1736
01:44:19.378 --> 01:44:23.842
Ethan Thomas calls himself
a man of faith.

1737
01:44:28.387 --> 01:44:31.516
I, on the other hand,
am a woman of doubt.

1738
01:44:35.478 --> 01:44:38.355
Angels and demons.

1739
01:44:38.356 --> 01:44:40.150
God and the devil.

1740
01:44:44.196 --> 01:44:47.365
These things either exist,
or they do not exist.

1741
01:44:50.368 --> 01:44:52.285
Are we all alone in this life?

1742
01:44:52.286 --> 01:44:54.413
Or are we not alone?

1743
01:44:55.665 --> 01:44:57.750
Either thought is astonishing.

1744
01:45:01.295 --> 01:45:03.505
Do I really believe
that this tragedy

1745
01:45:03.506 --> 01:45:05.716
is the work of the devil?

1746
01:45:05.717 --> 01:45:07.343
To be honest, I don't know.

1747
01:45:09.095 --> 01:45:12.597
But I cannot deny
that it's possible.

1748
01:45:12.598 --> 01:45:14.766
The prosecution
wants you to believe

1749
01:45:14.767 --> 01:45:18.020
that Emily's psychotic epileptic
disorder was a fact,

1750
01:45:18.021 --> 01:45:22.315
because facts leave no room
for reasonable doubt.

1751
01:45:22.316 --> 01:45:25.527
But this trial isn't
about facts.

1752
01:45:25.528 --> 01:45:28.822
This trial is
about possibilities.

1753
01:45:28.823 --> 01:45:31.825
Is it a fact that Emily
was a hypersensitive,

1754
01:45:31.826 --> 01:45:33.451
as Dr. Adani suggests?

1755
01:45:33.452 --> 01:45:37.455
A person... who's more likely,
by her very nature,

1756
01:45:37.456 --> 01:45:40.458
to become possessed?

1757
01:45:40.459 --> 01:45:45.338
I can't say that,
but the question is...

1758
01:45:45.339 --> 01:45:46.549
is it possible?

1759
01:45:48.509 --> 01:45:52.596
Is it a fact that Gambutrol
anesthetized Emily's brain

1760
01:45:52.597 --> 01:45:56.309
so that the exorcism ritual
was rendered ineffective?

1761
01:45:58.186 --> 01:45:59.938
I can't be sure of that.

1762
01:46:02.565 --> 01:46:03.816
But is it possible?

1763
01:46:05.193 --> 01:46:09.488
Is it a fact that Emily
was beloved by God?

1764
01:46:11.449 --> 01:46:15.160
And that after her exorcism,
she chose to suffer till the end

1765
01:46:15.161 --> 01:46:18.330
so that we might believe in
a more magical world?

1766
01:46:18.331 --> 01:46:22.751
A world where the spiritual
realm really exists?

1767
01:46:22.752 --> 01:46:24.837
I can't say that's a fact.

1768
01:46:25.922 --> 01:46:28.466
But ask yourself:

1769
01:46:30.135 --> 01:46:31.510
Is it possible?

1770
01:46:32.929 --> 01:46:35.180
It's what Emily believed.

1771
01:46:35.181 --> 01:46:36.932
It's what Father Moore believed.

1772
01:46:36.933 --> 01:46:40.602
And that sincere belief
is what determined her choices

1773
01:46:40.603 --> 01:46:41.853
and his.

1774
01:46:41.854 --> 01:46:45.566
Now, for the most
important question:

1775
01:46:47.152 --> 01:46:49.903
Is Father Richard Moore guilty

1776
01:46:49.904 --> 01:46:54.158
beyond a reasonable doubt
of negligent homicide?

1777
01:46:54.159 --> 01:46:56.076
Did he, in fact,

1778
01:46:56.077 --> 01:46:59.246
neglect Emily's needs
in such a way

1779
01:46:59.247 --> 01:47:01.957
that her death
is now on his hands?

1780
01:47:01.958 --> 01:47:02.958
No!

1781
01:47:02.959 --> 01:47:06.128
That is not a fact.

1782
01:47:06.129 --> 01:47:09.298
It is not a fact
that Emily was epileptic.

1783
01:47:09.299 --> 01:47:13.510
It is not a fact
that she was psychotic.

1784
01:47:13.511 --> 01:47:15.762
Facts...

1785
01:47:15.763 --> 01:47:18.891
leave no room for possibilities.

1786
01:47:20.518 --> 01:47:22.060
The only fact,

1787
01:47:22.061 --> 01:47:27.440
the only thing I know
beyond a doubt in this case,

1788
01:47:27.441 --> 01:47:31.320
is that Father Moore loved Emily
with his whole heart.

1789
01:47:31.321 --> 01:47:34.739
He did everything
in his power to help her.

1790
01:47:34.740 --> 01:47:39.871
He has risked his very freedom
so we could hear her story.

1791
01:47:46.336 --> 01:47:48.003
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

1792
01:47:48.004 --> 01:47:51.424
in my job I sometimes have
to defend bad men.

1793
01:47:52.925 --> 01:47:55.636
Father Richard Moore
is not one of them.

1794
01:47:59.098 --> 01:48:01.099
Don't send a good man to prison.

1795
01:48:01.100 --> 01:48:03.018
I'm not asking
that you believe everything

1796
01:48:03.019 --> 01:48:04.561
that Father Moore believes.

1797
01:48:04.562 --> 01:48:07.232
I'm simply asking that
you believe in Father Moore.

1798
01:48:24.665 --> 01:48:27.251
JUDGE: Madam Foreman,
has the jury reached a verdict?

1799
01:48:27.252 --> 01:48:28.794
We have, Your Honor.

1800
01:48:40.973 --> 01:48:43.017
Please read the verdict
out loud.

1801
01:48:47.605 --> 01:48:50.982
"In the case of <i>The People
v. Father Richard Moore,</i>

1802
01:48:50.983 --> 01:48:53.985
"we, the jury,
find the defendant...

1803
01:48:53.986 --> 01:48:57.115
guilty of negligent homicide."

1804
01:48:58.574 --> 01:49:01.243
JUDGE: The court thanks
the jury for its service.

1805
01:49:01.244 --> 01:49:06.539
Sentencing for this case
will be set for April 3rd.

1806
01:49:06.540 --> 01:49:08.250
Your Honor,
if it pleases the court,

1807
01:49:08.251 --> 01:49:10.252
Father Moore requested

1808
01:49:10.253 --> 01:49:12.379
at the start of trial
that if found guilty,

1809
01:49:12.380 --> 01:49:14.256
he would be sentenced
immediately.

1810
01:49:14.257 --> 01:49:16.425
Yes, I recall that.

1811
01:49:16.426 --> 01:49:18.385
Does the prosecution
have any objection

1812
01:49:18.386 --> 01:49:20.012
to expedited sentencing?

1813
01:49:21.597 --> 01:49:22.932
Very well.

1814
01:49:26.852 --> 01:49:27.936
Father Richard Moore,

1815
01:49:27.937 --> 01:49:30.272
do you understand this sentence,

1816
01:49:30.273 --> 01:49:31.731
which has been found
against you?

1817
01:49:31.732 --> 01:49:33.108
Yes, Your Honor.

1818
01:49:33.109 --> 01:49:35.568
And do you understand
the gravity of this crime?

1819
01:49:35.569 --> 01:49:37.321
That you may, under the law,

1820
01:49:37.322 --> 01:49:40.198
be sentenced to a term
of up to 10 years?

1821
01:49:40.199 --> 01:49:41.616
Yes, I do.

1822
01:49:41.617 --> 01:49:43.785
Are there any statements
you would like to make

1823
01:49:43.786 --> 01:49:45.620
before I impose this sentence?

1824
01:49:45.621 --> 01:49:46.788
No, Your Honor.

1825
01:49:46.789 --> 01:49:49.958
Very well.
Excuse me, Your Honor...

1826
01:49:49.959 --> 01:49:52.043
but the jury would like
to make a recommendation

1827
01:49:52.044 --> 01:49:53.838
regarding the sentence.
Objection.

1828
01:49:54.839 --> 01:49:56.465
Sit down, counselor.

1829
01:49:56.466 --> 01:49:59.511
It's only a recommendation,
and I would like to hear it.

1830
01:50:02.472 --> 01:50:05.224
We recommend a sentence
of time served.

1831
01:50:15.151 --> 01:50:16.694
I'll accept that.

1832
01:50:21.491 --> 01:50:23.201
You are guilty, Father Moore.

1833
01:50:24.243 --> 01:50:25.744
And you are free to go.

1834
01:50:27.372 --> 01:50:29.331
This court is dismissed.

1835
01:50:29.332 --> 01:50:30.542
All rise.

1836
01:50:33.044 --> 01:50:35.338
[♪♪♪]

1837
01:50:38.174 --> 01:50:39.258
Thank you.

1838
01:51:06.869 --> 01:51:10.163
Well, you shocked us all.

1839
01:51:10.164 --> 01:51:12.916
Everyone at the firm
sees this as another victory.

1840
01:51:12.917 --> 01:51:15.043
The archdiocese is pleased.

1841
01:51:15.044 --> 01:51:18.213
They feel the trial has raised
public interest in the Church.

1842
01:51:18.214 --> 01:51:19.923
Have you seen the news?

1843
01:51:19.924 --> 01:51:22.509
There's our priest, leaving
the courthouse a free man,

1844
01:51:22.510 --> 01:51:24.761
right next to you.

1845
01:51:24.762 --> 01:51:27.223
Just like James Van Hopper.

1846
01:51:28.682 --> 01:51:30.975
All right, I'll say it.
I was wrong.

1847
01:51:30.976 --> 01:51:32.603
But I'm ready to make it right.

1848
01:51:32.604 --> 01:51:36.065
I'm offering you
a full partnership in the firm.

1849
01:51:38.984 --> 01:51:40.069
Keep it.

1850
01:51:50.788 --> 01:51:52.915
[RAIN PATTERING]

1851
01:51:53.749 --> 01:51:55.209
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

1852
01:52:05.470 --> 01:52:07.972
Will you be able to return
to your parish?

1853
01:52:11.643 --> 01:52:13.644
I can't go back.

1854
01:52:13.645 --> 01:52:14.979
Not now.

1855
01:52:17.523 --> 01:52:20.817
Once you've looked
into the darkness...

1856
01:52:20.818 --> 01:52:24.363
I think you carry it with you
for the rest of your life.

1857
01:52:28.284 --> 01:52:29.619
What about you?

1858
01:52:31.621 --> 01:52:34.373
I believe you've seen
the darkness too.

1859
01:52:38.628 --> 01:52:39.712
I don't know.

1860
01:52:42.840 --> 01:52:45.384
I'm not sure what I've seen.

1861
01:52:46.802 --> 01:52:49.555
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

1862
01:52:54.310 --> 01:52:56.186
Who chose the epitaph?

1863
01:52:56.187 --> 01:52:58.438
I did.

1864
01:52:58.439 --> 01:53:03.026
It's from the second chapter
of Philippians, verse 12.

1865
01:53:03.027 --> 01:53:06.113
Emily recited it to me
the night before she died.

1866
01:54:13.013 --> 01:54:16.392
[♪♪♪]

1867
01:54:44.295 --> 01:54:48.382
[♪♪♪]

